shameful /ˈʃeɪmfʊl/

1. ADJ If you describe a person's action or attitude as shameful , you think that it is so bad that the person ought to be ashamed. 可耻的 [表不满] 

例： ...the most shameful episode in U.S. naval history. …美国海军史上最耻辱的一段历史。 

2. shamefully ADV 可耻地 

例： At times they have been shamefully neglected. 有时他们被可耻地忽略了。

